						<summary>

						<p>Stone standing near the Girls School.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription referring itself to the reign of Tribhuvanamalla is dated in Chālukya-Vikrama year (lost), Chaitra, śu. 5, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It describes the learned <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of the village. Seems to record a gift of land by several individuals.</p>						

						</summary>
